<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/429: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-24T18:00:00-04:00">June 24,
                                    1935—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>149. One of our missions in Europe has reported in strict confidence that
                            it has learned the British Government intends to call a “general naval
                            conference”, including, among others, the Soviet Government, and that
                            the latter has been officially informed to this effect. Please cable us
                            any confirmatory information you may have been able discreetly to
                            obtain.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>